WEBVTT

1
00:00:57.826 --> 00:00:59.209
Daniel!

2
00:01:00.495 --> 00:01:01.841
Mother!

3
00:01:02.559 --> 00:01:05.379
- When did you arrive?
- I arrived yesterday.

4
00:01:21.257 --> 00:01:23.310
So long.

5
00:01:29.262 --> 00:01:30.729
Hello.

6
00:01:33.023 --> 00:01:34.589
Hello.

7
00:01:35.549 --> 00:01:37.996
I've heard a lot about you.

8
00:01:41.296 --> 00:01:43.909
For Daniel, of course.

9
00:01:45.260 --> 00:01:46.410
Oh really?

10
00:01:46.410 --> 00:01:49.043
Every time I talked about you, I wondered.

11
00:01:51.130 --> 00:01:52.042
About me?

12
00:01:52.042 --> 00:01:54.703
I was curious about you.

13
00:01:54.703 --> 00:01:58.443
How would you be, how would you look.

14
00:01:59.016 --> 00:02:00.943
But you...

15
00:02:06.885 --> 00:02:09.691
you have dignity.

16
00:02:09.691 --> 00:02:11.786
That is,

17
00:02:11.786 --> 00:02:14.325
You are more impressive than I imagined.

18
00:02:15.826 --> 00:02:19.059
When I say "awesome",
It's a compliment, right?

19
00:02:19.059 --> 00:02:20.298
Yes.

20
00:02:21.998 --> 00:02:23.525
Daniel!

21
00:02:24.838 --> 00:02:26.155
Hello, Daniel.

22
00:02:26.155 --> 00:02:28.777
You were amazing today.

23
00:02:28.777 --> 00:02:30.811
- Hello.
- Hello.

24
00:02:30.811 --> 00:02:32.850
- I'm Ji Min's mom.
- Hello, you must be Ji Min.

25
00:02:32.850 --> 00:02:35.609
You were wonderful, you did a great job.

26
00:02:35.609 --> 00:02:37.669
I always thought Daniel was handsome,

27
00:02:37.669 --> 00:02:40.282
and now I see that it runs in the family.

28
00:02:42.962 --> 00:02:45.048
- Hello.
- I'm glad to see you.

29
00:03:14.032 --> 00:03:15.431
Jun Kyung.

30
00:03:23.553 --> 00:03:25.019
I'm sorry.

31
00:03:26.626 --> 00:03:28.346
Why are you apologizing?

32
00:03:28.346 --> 00:03:31.076
I didn't expect it to appear like this.

33
00:03:31.076 --> 00:03:32.436
Of course yes,

34
00:03:32.436 --> 00:03:33.852
She is Daniel's mother.

35
00:03:36.769 --> 00:03:38.709
-Do Hyun.
- Yeah?

36
00:03:39.349 --> 00:03:41.626
You should see Daniel's teacher.

37
00:03:41.626 --> 00:03:43.649
I already greeted her.

38
00:03:50.206 --> 00:03:52.552
Wait a second, don't leave yet.

39
00:03:56.513 --> 00:03:58.746
Why are you so nervous?

40
00:04:01.070 --> 00:04:02.779
Wouldn't it be?

41
00:04:03.609 --> 00:04:04.929
Because?

42
00:04:06.840 --> 00:04:08.803
For me?

43
00:04:10.519 --> 00:04:12.479
Hey, everyone here looks uncomfortable except...

44
00:04:12.479 --> 00:04:14.398
My name is Im Yun Ju.

45
00:04:20.907 --> 00:04:22.993
...except you.

46
00:04:26.798 --> 00:04:29.004
Does that amuse you?

47
00:04:30.138 --> 00:04:32.145
Let's have dinner together.

48
00:04:32.145 --> 00:04:35.144
You came all this way to see Daniel play.

49
00:04:39.571 --> 00:04:41.656
Yes, I'm going out.

50
00:04:41.656 --> 00:04:43.814
You can start without me.

51
00:04:43.814 --> 00:04:45.687
It's okay, I'm sorry.

52
00:04:48.020 --> 00:04:50.324
Even if it's late, finish before you leave.

53
00:04:50.324 --> 00:04:52.055
Understood.

54
00:04:52.055 --> 00:04:53.312
TRUE.

55
00:04:53.312 --> 00:04:55.633
Regarding field practice
of the second years...

56
00:04:55.633 --> 00:04:57.015
Wait.

57
00:04:57.836 --> 00:04:59.829
You know the password to my computer, right?

58
00:05:01.070 --> 00:05:03.823
- But I'm in the middle of this...
- This is more urgent.

59
00:05:07.715 --> 00:05:09.413
If you are hungry, order something.

60
00:05:09.413 --> 00:05:10.754
OK.

61
00:05:10.754 --> 00:05:13.847
- Make the notification first.
- Yes sir.

62
00:05:26.111 --> 00:05:28.036
- Hello.
- Finally

63
00:05:28.036 --> 00:05:30.245
I pressed the button!

64
00:05:30.245 --> 00:05:31.904
What button?

65
00:05:32.613 --> 00:05:34.311
What a cold response

66
00:05:34.311 --> 00:05:37.478
at the beginning of your girlfriend's trip
to become a successful writer.

67
00:05:38.200 --> 00:05:40.701
I told you, today was the deadline.

68
00:05:40.701 --> 00:05:42.365
I delivered it!

69
00:05:42.365 --> 00:05:44.202
Clear!

70
00:05:44.202 --> 00:05:47.026
How about a pork chop and a beer?

71
00:05:47.026 --> 00:05:49.727
We could celebrate together.

72
00:05:49.727 --> 00:05:52.203
Okay, I'll finish as soon as possible.

73
00:05:52.203 --> 00:05:53.548
See you later.

74
00:05:53.548 --> 00:05:55.017
Come in, please.

75
00:05:57.504 --> 00:05:59.069
Isn't the teacher here?

76
00:05:59.069 --> 00:06:00.662
It's already gone.

77
00:06:04.001 --> 00:06:05.327
Because?

78
00:06:12.597 --> 00:06:14.186
Well...

79
00:06:14.186 --> 00:06:16.305
Can I hand this in now?

80
00:06:17.026 --> 00:06:19.632
- You should have done it before.
- I'm sorry.

81
00:06:22.112 --> 00:06:24.025
And this too.

82
00:06:28.113 --> 00:06:30.224
- Thank you.
- Bye bye.

83
00:06:30.224 --> 00:06:31.452
Bye bye.

84
00:06:55.219 --> 00:06:57.225
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

85
00:06:59.219 --> 00:07:00.904
It's still very clean.

86
00:07:00.904 --> 00:07:02.926
I almost feel bad taking it.

87
00:07:02.926 --> 00:07:05.526
I'm glad they put it to good use.

88
00:07:05.526 --> 00:07:06.870
Thank you.

89
00:07:06.870 --> 00:07:08.979
- I will take good care of her.
- Thank you.

90
00:07:10.150 --> 00:07:12.823
Live well in that nice house.

91
00:07:25.466 --> 00:07:26.680
Ja Yeong,

92
00:07:27.301 --> 00:07:29.500
are you okay?

93
00:07:29.500 --> 00:07:32.384
Now it is an empty house, only memories remain.

94
00:07:32.384 --> 00:07:34.370
I don't care anymore.

95
00:07:35.330 --> 00:07:37.454
Let's eat something delicious.

96
00:07:37.454 --> 00:07:38.760
What do you want?

97
00:07:38.760 --> 00:07:40.546
Whatever you want.

98
00:07:42.240 --> 00:07:44.186
Well, what I want is...

99
00:07:48.939 --> 00:07:51.085
Is this what you wanted?

100
00:07:51.085 --> 00:07:52.696
They say the best food in the world

101
00:07:52.696 --> 00:07:54.338
the ramen that someone prepares for you

102
00:07:54.338 --> 00:07:56.058
open sky.

103
00:07:56.973 --> 00:07:58.238
I guess you're right.

104
00:07:58.238 --> 00:08:01.112
Eat the ramen you made with you

105
00:08:01.112 --> 00:08:04.786
It tastes better than noodles in the Alps.

106
00:08:04.786 --> 00:08:07.159
I didn't do it, it was the machine.

107
00:08:08.759 --> 00:08:10.592
Be careful, it's leaking.

108
00:08:18.919 --> 00:08:21.119
Still don't feel like working?

109
00:08:21.119 --> 00:08:22.425
Yes.

110
00:08:23.472 --> 00:08:25.653
When Bom got sick,

111
00:08:25.653 --> 00:08:28.693
I took a break from work
to be by his side a little more.

112
00:08:28.693 --> 00:08:30.690
It's been six months now.

113
00:08:30.690 --> 00:08:32.810
Yes, time flies.

114
00:08:40.270 --> 00:08:42.096
Those birds...

115
00:08:43.857 --> 00:08:46.853
They fly freely wherever they want,

116
00:08:46.853 --> 00:08:48.591
But when they get old and tired,

117
00:08:48.591 --> 00:08:50.278
and they can no longer fly away,

118
00:08:50.278 --> 00:08:51.959
what's happening?

119
00:08:53.900 --> 00:08:55.313
Does it

120
00:08:56.320 --> 00:08:59.766
They end up settling somewhere,
becoming resident birds?

121
00:09:04.833 --> 00:09:06.370
Maybe.

122
00:09:07.614 --> 00:09:09.640
I had never thought about it.

123
00:09:10.163 --> 00:09:11.807
It's a little sad.

124
00:09:11.807 --> 00:09:13.760
I think it's fine.

125
00:09:15.643 --> 00:09:18.749
They have spent their entire lives
chasing good seasons.

126
00:09:30.147 --> 00:09:32.806
A place where you are the first
to see the flowers open,

127
00:09:34.366 --> 00:09:37.092
to feel the sun on your skin,

128
00:09:39.032 --> 00:09:41.651
in stepping on fallen leaves,

129
00:09:42.759 --> 00:09:45.272
to see the snow melt.

130
00:09:46.999 --> 00:09:48.945
If there is such a place,

131
00:09:49.532 --> 00:09:51.403
be a resident bird,

132
00:09:51.403 --> 00:09:54.027
that stays in one place,
receives and dismisses people,

133
00:09:54.027 --> 00:09:55.783
It would be nice.

134
00:09:58.643 --> 00:10:01.409
I have lived my entire life as a migratory bird.

135
00:10:18.216 --> 00:10:20.816
Who says the pork chop
Does it go well with beer?

136
00:10:21.622 --> 00:10:24.942
That's poor people consoling themselves.

137
00:10:24.942 --> 00:10:27.815
The pork chop goes with whiskey.

138
00:10:30.342 --> 00:10:32.475
At least 30 years.

139
00:10:37.570 --> 00:10:39.226
What's happening?

140
00:10:39.226 --> 00:10:41.619
Your face doesn't say "party."

141
00:10:42.546 --> 00:10:45.971
While everyone improved their averages
and built careers,

142
00:10:45.971 --> 00:10:47.291
what was I doing?

143
00:10:47.291 --> 00:10:50.179
you were very busy
falling in love and dating.

144
00:10:54.165 --> 00:10:56.491
I sent you my manuscript

145
00:10:56.491 --> 00:10:59.222
thinking you would be perfect
as a critic of romantic novels,

146
00:10:59.222 --> 00:11:00.900
and you didn't even finish it,

147
00:11:00.900 --> 00:11:02.604
right?

148
00:11:02.604 --> 00:11:04.073
I'm sorry,

149
00:11:04.073 --> 00:11:05.824
but I know it will work.

150
00:11:05.824 --> 00:11:07.509
Of course!

151
00:11:07.509 --> 00:11:08.775
Do you remember the plan

152
00:11:08.775 --> 00:11:11.068
What did I do when I joined the publishing house?

153
00:11:11.068 --> 00:11:12.847
after I graduate, right?

154
00:11:12.847 --> 00:11:14.697
I would save 24 million won

155
00:11:14.697 --> 00:11:17.327
to write until I turned 30.

156
00:11:17.327 --> 00:11:19.130
Then I would quit my job.

157
00:11:19.130 --> 00:11:20.778
and I would enter the contest

158
00:11:20.778 --> 00:11:22.585
in the spring of my 29th birthday.

159
00:11:22.585 --> 00:11:25.343
And when the results came out in three months,

160
00:11:26.783 --> 00:11:28.228
I would publish my book

161
00:11:28.228 --> 00:11:29.883
before turning 30.

162
00:11:31.989 --> 00:11:34.375
Just as I planned.

163
00:11:39.375 --> 00:11:40.400
Have you finished drinking yet?

164
00:11:40.400 --> 00:11:43.399
It's too early to drink
just for entering the contest.

165
00:11:44.277 --> 00:11:46.970
Something very good is coming soon.

166
00:11:47.443 --> 00:11:50.076
That day is when I will finish this bottle.

167
00:11:53.043 --> 00:11:54.476
Do you really think

168
00:11:54.976 --> 00:11:57.576
that life is going as you planned?

169
00:12:00.059 --> 00:12:02.100
Why are you always so pessimistic?

170
00:12:02.100 --> 00:12:04.413
Why are you always so optimistic?

171
00:12:04.413 --> 00:12:05.804
I am not

172
00:12:05.804 --> 00:12:08.933
neither pessimistic nor optimistic.

173
00:12:09.987 --> 00:12:11.846
I am idealistic.

174
00:12:19.555 --> 00:12:22.575
If that woman had been a little more educated,

175
00:12:23.729 --> 00:12:26.515
or if he didn't look younger than me,

176
00:12:26.515 --> 00:12:28.634
or if she wasn't so pretty...

177
00:12:29.765 --> 00:12:31.848
Would I feel that way anyway?

178
00:12:31.848 --> 00:12:33.816
Did you know?

179
00:12:33.816 --> 00:12:36.194
He told you: "Dinner with your family."

180
00:12:36.194 --> 00:12:37.830
That was too much.

181
00:12:37.830 --> 00:12:39.663
It was the worst, wasn't it?

182
00:12:41.403 --> 00:12:43.540
It's understandable.

183
00:12:43.540 --> 00:12:45.288
Your current boyfriend's ex,

184
00:12:45.288 --> 00:12:47.634
his son, all four of them there.

185
00:12:48.334 --> 00:12:49.706
Anyone would go crazy.

186
00:12:49.706 --> 00:12:51.830
They seemed like the perfect family,

187
00:12:51.830 --> 00:12:56.223
and I am a villain without an invitation
that appeared on the scene.

188
00:12:56.223 --> 00:12:57.847
I completely understand that feeling.

189
00:12:57.847 --> 00:12:59.698
Every time I go to meetings

190
00:12:59.698 --> 00:13:02.444
from my in-laws, uncles, aunts, cousins,

191
00:13:02.444 --> 00:13:05.290
everyone is strangely happy

192
00:13:05.290 --> 00:13:08.890
and I'm the only stranger involved in his family.

193
00:13:09.503 --> 00:13:12.122
My husband tries a lot

194
00:13:12.660 --> 00:13:15.167
to understand the situation,
stuck in the middle.

195
00:13:15.167 --> 00:13:18.519
Don't you realize
Does that make me like him less?

196
00:13:18.519 --> 00:13:20.490
Children, daddy has arrived!

197
00:13:20.490 --> 00:13:22.262
- Daddy!
- Daddy.

198
00:13:22.262 --> 00:13:24.709
Were they having fun?

199
00:13:24.709 --> 00:13:26.102
What is this?

200
00:13:26.102 --> 00:13:27.215
He really doesn't know.

201
00:13:27.215 --> 00:13:28.990
Jun Kyung, when did you arrive?

202
00:13:28.990 --> 00:13:30.323
When did you arrive?

203
00:13:30.323 --> 00:13:34.176
I was very bored at the hospital today.
You came to save me.

204
00:13:34.176 --> 00:13:35.529
What happened?

205
00:13:35.529 --> 00:13:37.250
They didn't go very far without me, did they?

206
00:13:37.250 --> 00:13:39.109
What's happening?

207
00:13:39.109 --> 00:13:40.263
Is it serious?

208
00:13:40.263 --> 00:13:41.796
Is it a serious situation?

209
00:13:41.796 --> 00:13:44.470
Wait. I will give you the best advice in the world.

210
00:13:44.470 --> 00:13:46.370
Let me change quickly.

211
00:13:46.370 --> 00:13:48.116
Don't go.

212
00:13:52.562 --> 00:13:54.337
Eat pizza too.

213
00:13:54.337 --> 00:13:55.757
Thank you.

214
00:14:00.083 --> 00:14:01.529
It looks delicious.

215
00:14:03.251 --> 00:14:05.238
Do you want a glass of wine?

216
00:14:06.485 --> 00:14:07.835
I'm fine.

217
00:14:07.835 --> 00:14:09.581
If you want, go ahead.

218
00:14:10.463 --> 00:14:12.329
I stopped drinking.

219
00:14:18.123 --> 00:14:19.523
By the way,

220
00:14:20.336 --> 00:14:22.482
Shouldn't you come next week?

221
00:14:23.703 --> 00:14:25.462
I came before.

222
00:14:26.357 --> 00:14:28.542
I also wanted to see Daniel's recital.

223
00:14:34.182 --> 00:14:35.955
You should have warned us.

224
00:14:36.749 --> 00:14:39.389
I wanted to surprise them.

225
00:14:39.389 --> 00:14:42.146
Yes, it was a total surprise.

226
00:14:42.146 --> 00:14:43.575
Right?

227
00:14:44.175 --> 00:14:45.868
I saw everything from the beginning.

228
00:14:45.868 --> 00:14:47.779
- From the beginning?
- Yes.

229
00:14:47.779 --> 00:14:49.988
You were incredible.

230
00:14:49.988 --> 00:14:53.826
Birth rates fell,
so I walk on eggshells.

231
00:14:53.826 --> 00:14:58.440
There are more and more psychiatric patients
and everyone asks for Hyeong Jun.

232
00:14:58.440 --> 00:15:00.440
I thought things would calm down

233
00:15:00.440 --> 00:15:04.533
Now that the children are older,
So I gave everything with confidence,

234
00:15:04.533 --> 00:15:06.371
but the only thing that grew

235
00:15:06.371 --> 00:15:08.530
It was my knowledge to make liquor

236
00:15:08.530 --> 00:15:10.310
and my abdominal fat.

237
00:15:10.310 --> 00:15:13.375
And I don't even have anything to wear
for Dr. Hong's wedding.

238
00:15:13.375 --> 00:15:16.906
And it's not that I have "nothing good to wear",

239
00:15:16.906 --> 00:15:19.719
This time I have nothing at all.

240
00:15:27.583 --> 00:15:29.063
I'm sorry.

241
00:15:29.063 --> 00:15:30.750
That's not comforting, is it?

242
00:15:30.750 --> 00:15:32.009
No.

243
00:15:37.072 --> 00:15:39.105
I don't know why, but this spring

244
00:15:39.936 --> 00:15:42.189
It feels especially bitter.

245
00:15:42.835 --> 00:15:45.114
As if it was going to be very cruel.

246
00:15:47.929 --> 00:15:50.140
The children finally fell asleep.

247
00:15:50.140 --> 00:15:52.326
What's happening? What's the real mess?

248
00:15:52.326 --> 00:15:53.650
Gosh, the alcohol is over.

249
00:15:53.650 --> 00:15:55.850
Wait, don't start yet.

250
00:16:03.385 --> 00:16:06.439
Why Do Hyun

251
00:16:06.439 --> 00:16:08.272
hasn't he called you?

252
00:16:15.123 --> 00:16:16.307
Thank you

253
00:16:16.307 --> 00:16:18.327
for taking care of Daniel.

254
00:16:20.067 --> 00:16:21.397
It's nothing,

255
00:16:21.397 --> 00:16:23.210
It's what I should do.

256
00:16:24.617 --> 00:16:26.808
Of course yes,

257
00:16:26.808 --> 00:16:28.848
you are his father.

258
00:16:31.303 --> 00:16:33.923
You're moving out this month, right?

259
00:16:35.064 --> 00:16:36.264
Yes.

260
00:16:40.896 --> 00:16:43.476
It's pretty. I mean, Jun Kyung.

261
00:16:47.656 --> 00:16:50.829
Still charming, I guess.

262
00:16:51.763 --> 00:16:53.356
Did you find a place?

263
00:16:55.576 --> 00:16:57.196
Do you change the subject?

264
00:16:57.683 --> 00:16:59.834
I'll stay at my mom's house for now.

265
00:16:59.834 --> 00:17:02.100
He's in Canada, visiting my brother.

266
00:17:07.296 --> 00:17:09.887
I didn't expect a warm welcome,

267
00:17:09.887 --> 00:17:11.927
but you are exactly the same.

268
00:17:14.262 --> 00:17:15.553
That look on your face

269
00:17:15.553 --> 00:17:18.375
It's exactly how you looked
when I left Korea 16 years ago.

270
00:17:27.759 --> 00:17:29.299
You know,

271
00:17:30.047 --> 00:17:32.012
an ordinary day,

272
00:17:32.012 --> 00:17:34.220
I'm on the bus

273
00:17:34.220 --> 00:17:37.433
and someone is reading my book.

274
00:17:38.126 --> 00:17:40.044
- Yes.
- And then,

275
00:17:40.044 --> 00:17:41.949
I see that they read it.

276
00:17:42.819 --> 00:17:45.579
Don't you feel like your heart is going to explode?

277
00:17:47.680 --> 00:17:50.986
You don't want to be a big famous author.

278
00:17:50.986 --> 00:17:54.593
You don't need to write a <i>best seller</i>
or earn a lot of money.

279
00:17:54.593 --> 00:17:56.479
Do you only have that small dream?

280
00:17:57.180 --> 00:18:00.733
Although the pessimist
I kept showing him the cold reality,

281
00:18:01.233 --> 00:18:05.935
The idealist, strangely, felt at peace,

282
00:18:05.935 --> 00:18:09.121
and the drinks tasted sweet.

283
00:18:16.461 --> 00:18:18.134
- Bye bye.
- Bye bye.

284
00:18:19.415 --> 00:18:21.868
- You first.
- You first.

285
00:18:21.868 --> 00:18:23.253
- Leave.
- OK.

286
00:18:23.253 --> 00:18:24.559
- Bye bye.
- Bye bye.

287
00:18:29.989 --> 00:18:31.736
Do you want me to accompany you?

288
00:18:32.896 --> 00:18:34.122
Yes.

289
00:18:34.796 --> 00:18:35.996
Let's go.

290
00:18:37.776 --> 00:18:39.403
Will you accompany me again?

291
00:18:39.403 --> 00:18:41.089
I'm already getting tired.

292
00:18:41.089 --> 00:18:43.307
That? I'll be bored alone.

293
00:18:43.923 --> 00:18:45.187
No?

294
00:18:45.766 --> 00:18:47.579
So, stay at my house.

295
00:18:48.420 --> 00:18:49.853
Ought?

296
00:18:51.376 --> 00:18:52.779
Aren't you hungry?

297
00:18:57.240 --> 00:18:59.886
<i>A place where you are the first
to see the flowers open,</i>

298
00:19:01.446 --> 00:19:03.919
<i>in feeling the sun on the skin,</i>

299
00:19:05.206 --> 00:19:07.706
<i>in stepping on fallen leaves,</i>

300
00:19:08.820 --> 00:19:11.440
<i>in watching the snow melt.</i>

301
00:19:13.092 --> 00:19:15.846
<i>If there is such a place,</i>

302
00:19:15.846 --> 00:19:17.865
<i>be a resident bird,</i>

303
00:19:18.606 --> 00:19:21.766
<i>that stays in one place,
receives and dismisses people,</i>

304
00:19:21.766 --> 00:19:23.605
<i>it would be nice.</i>

305
00:19:26.643 --> 00:19:29.416
<i>I have lived my entire life as a migratory bird.</i>

306
00:19:43.555 --> 00:19:46.013
<i>Dad, I'm not going home tonight.</i>

307
00:19:46.013 --> 00:19:47.814
<i>Don't wait up for me.</i>

308
00:20:11.310 --> 00:20:13.009
Now it's an empty house,

309
00:20:14.403 --> 00:20:16.636
only memories remain.

310
00:20:19.663 --> 00:20:21.569
I don't mind.

311
00:20:34.990 --> 00:20:36.254
<i>That look on your face...</i>

312
00:20:36.254 --> 00:20:38.936
<i>it's exactly how you looked
when I left Korea 16 years ago.</i>

313
00:20:39.943 --> 00:20:43.169
<i>It seems like it will be warm forever,</i>

314
00:20:43.863 --> 00:20:45.683
<i>until, suddenly,</i>

315
00:20:45.683 --> 00:20:48.016
<i>that look appears,</i>

316
00:20:48.016 --> 00:20:49.745
<i>as if to say: "I'm exhausted."</i>

317
00:20:52.663 --> 00:20:55.679
<i>That's the look he makes</i>

318
00:20:56.420 --> 00:20:57.853
<i>someone leave.</i>

319
00:21:08.531 --> 00:21:11.790
[Missed call: Do Hyun]

320
00:21:24.570 --> 00:21:29.150
<i>Do you know the difference
between loneliness and isolation?</i>

321
00:21:30.030 --> 00:21:34.322
<i>Solitude is the joy of choosing to be alone.</i>

322
00:21:35.063 --> 00:21:40.569
<i>Isolation is pain
of being alone against your will.</i>

323
00:21:42.184 --> 00:21:44.543
<i>So, now,</i>

324
00:21:44.543 --> 00:21:47.018
<i>what do you feel?</i>

325
00:21:48.363 --> 00:21:49.910
<i>Loneliness</i>

326
00:21:49.910 --> 00:21:52.863
<i>or isolation?</i>

327
00:22:09.660 --> 00:22:11.400
Wow.

328
00:22:11.400 --> 00:22:12.659
Just in time.

329
00:22:14.547 --> 00:22:16.846
I also wanted a beer.

330
00:22:25.430 --> 00:22:26.943
I'm sorry.

331
00:22:36.526 --> 00:22:38.410
Why do you have to apologize?

332
00:22:39.213 --> 00:22:40.599
I am...

333
00:22:41.872 --> 00:22:43.605
the one who should apologize.

334
00:23:02.849 --> 00:23:04.686
I'm very tired today.

335
00:23:07.848 --> 00:23:09.361
I'm going in.

336
00:23:16.826 --> 00:23:18.726
You said I didn't do anything wrong...

337
00:23:20.912 --> 00:23:23.238
But you treat me like I did it.

338
00:23:29.459 --> 00:23:31.612
Clear. Why do you make me feel this way?

339
00:23:33.875 --> 00:23:36.146
I know you have a son,

340
00:23:36.146 --> 00:23:39.038
I knew that Yun Ju would return,

341
00:23:39.038 --> 00:23:40.978
but when we were standing there
the three together,

342
00:23:40.978 --> 00:23:43.351
I was the only one who looked stupid.

343
00:23:51.066 --> 00:23:54.459
I know that nobody did anything wrong,

344
00:23:56.313 --> 00:23:59.037
But I hate myself for feeling this way.

345
00:23:59.037 --> 00:24:01.423
I feel pathetic and childish.

346
00:24:04.614 --> 00:24:06.400
I hate this.

347
00:24:08.234 --> 00:24:09.787
See?

348
00:24:12.686 --> 00:24:14.483
I'm the one who's wrong.

349
00:24:15.790 --> 00:24:17.903
You've always been like this,

350
00:24:19.699 --> 00:24:22.050
the two years we have been together.

351
00:24:22.050 --> 00:24:24.119
When things get like this...

352
00:24:26.905 --> 00:24:28.798
you walk away first.

353
00:24:30.686 --> 00:24:32.465
You run.

354
00:24:33.347 --> 00:24:35.306
You hide.

355
00:25:02.446 --> 00:25:03.959
Therefore, I ask your forgiveness...

356
00:25:08.426 --> 00:25:09.946
for making you feel this way

357
00:25:11.140 --> 00:25:12.939
again.

358
00:25:38.180 --> 00:25:39.697
- Welcome.
- Hello.

359
00:25:39.697 --> 00:25:41.253
- Hello.
- Hello.

360
00:25:42.073 --> 00:25:44.145
- Beautiful mountains, right?
- Yes.

361
00:25:45.286 --> 00:25:46.592
Over here.

362
00:25:48.133 --> 00:25:50.230
This is the kitchen area.

363
00:25:50.230 --> 00:25:52.196
Good cold water pressure.

364
00:25:53.426 --> 00:25:54.917
Since it is small,

365
00:25:54.917 --> 00:25:57.010
There is not much to maintain.

366
00:26:00.617 --> 00:26:03.649
This is the office and the store.

367
00:26:03.649 --> 00:26:05.368
We have everything.

368
00:26:05.368 --> 00:26:07.037
Take a look.

369
00:26:08.613 --> 00:26:09.857
and here it is

370
00:26:09.857 --> 00:26:11.403
where we live

371
00:26:11.403 --> 00:26:13.546
my partner and I.

372
00:26:14.132 --> 00:26:15.625
Please come.

373
00:26:22.436 --> 00:26:24.176
I thought that only

374
00:26:24.689 --> 00:26:27.666
you had come to camp.

375
00:26:27.666 --> 00:26:29.845
I had no idea what you thought

376
00:26:29.845 --> 00:26:31.571
buy the place.

377
00:26:33.596 --> 00:26:37.616
I thought I'd try camping first,

378
00:26:38.749 --> 00:26:41.222
but plans never go well.

379
00:26:41.896 --> 00:26:43.555
Seeing this place,

380
00:26:45.056 --> 00:26:47.209
I feel like I would regret it if I let it go.

381
00:26:49.651 --> 00:26:51.127
You're sure?

382
00:26:51.127 --> 00:26:53.333
Is it really okay?

383
00:26:54.266 --> 00:26:55.813
What do you think?

384
00:26:56.739 --> 00:26:59.144
For me, it's okay, I'm alone,

385
00:26:59.144 --> 00:27:00.880
but you

386
00:27:00.880 --> 00:27:02.999
you have children.

387
00:27:06.356 --> 00:27:09.176
The anniversary is approaching
of my wife's death.

388
00:27:10.203 --> 00:27:12.189
Do you know what I regret the most?

389
00:27:13.703 --> 00:27:15.923
after losing her?

390
00:27:19.790 --> 00:27:21.576
I should have retired earlier.

391
00:27:22.962 --> 00:27:25.522
I should have spent more time with her.

392
00:27:30.349 --> 00:27:32.574
I already decided.

393
00:27:34.108 --> 00:27:36.428
She would have wanted him to live like this.

394
00:27:37.536 --> 00:27:39.056
and the children

395
00:27:39.810 --> 00:27:41.402
they will understand.

396
00:27:50.633 --> 00:27:52.211
Hey, Jun Seo.

397
00:27:52.211 --> 00:27:54.020
Dad,

398
00:27:54.020 --> 00:27:55.790
I think I'll be late again.

399
00:27:55.790 --> 00:27:57.580
Are you at home?

400
00:27:57.580 --> 00:27:58.894
No, I went out too.

401
00:27:58.894 --> 00:28:00.609
<i>Where are you?</i>

402
00:28:02.469 --> 00:28:04.247
Camping with Ja Yeong.

403
00:28:04.247 --> 00:28:07.378
<i>Sounds great, have fun with it.</i>

404
00:28:07.378 --> 00:28:09.313
<i>Don't stay at home all the time.</i>

405
00:28:10.551 --> 00:28:12.271
Jun Seo.

406
00:28:16.466 --> 00:28:18.332
By the way, did I tell you...?

407
00:28:22.326 --> 00:28:24.379
Did I give you your allowance?

408
00:28:25.473 --> 00:28:27.979
<i>Yes, I still have it, you gave it to me last week.</i>

409
00:28:27.979 --> 00:28:31.060
<i>Don't worry about me. Have fun, okay?</i>

410
00:28:31.060 --> 00:28:32.370
Okay.

411
00:28:37.816 --> 00:28:39.909
They will understand.

412
00:28:47.850 --> 00:28:50.497
Is the house in your name?

413
00:28:51.469 --> 00:28:52.755
Yes.

414
00:28:53.629 --> 00:28:56.850
Did your children help you financially?
when did you buy it?

415
00:28:56.850 --> 00:28:58.450
No.

416
00:28:58.450 --> 00:29:00.838
So what's the problem?

417
00:29:00.838 --> 00:29:03.176
It's your house, you just want to sell it.

418
00:29:04.017 --> 00:29:05.861
I wonder

419
00:29:05.861 --> 00:29:09.580
yes I'm being selfish
and I only pursue my own happiness.

420
00:29:09.580 --> 00:29:12.090
Even sins of the heart are sins, right?

421
00:29:12.090 --> 00:29:14.547
All humans are selfish.

422
00:29:14.547 --> 00:29:17.655
That's what I'm saying, maybe I'm too selfish.

423
00:29:17.655 --> 00:29:20.015
So, don't sell the house. Please.

424
00:29:21.308 --> 00:29:23.400
Hey, Chang Sik.

425
00:29:23.400 --> 00:29:25.393
My life matters too, right?

426
00:29:26.047 --> 00:29:27.413
Listen,

427
00:29:27.960 --> 00:29:30.131
Yesterday another man came to confess.

428
00:29:30.131 --> 00:29:33.997
He said he heard an important piece of information
and asked if he should buy shares.

429
00:29:34.577 --> 00:29:37.463
He said his wife would kill him if she found out.

430
00:29:38.430 --> 00:29:41.042
Do you know what I told him?

431
00:29:41.042 --> 00:29:42.823
Don't know.

432
00:29:42.823 --> 00:29:44.574
I told him:

433
00:29:44.574 --> 00:29:47.800
"Go home right now
and talk to her before she finds out.

434
00:29:48.794 --> 00:29:51.145
And if you make a lot of money,

435
00:29:51.145 --> 00:29:53.751
"Donate more to the church."

436
00:29:55.705 --> 00:29:59.591
What am I? Fund manager?
Or a real estate investor?

437
00:30:00.895 --> 00:30:02.289
Did you know?

438
00:30:02.289 --> 00:30:03.893
Those decisions

439
00:30:03.893 --> 00:30:06.276
They are not for God or for me.

440
00:30:06.276 --> 00:30:09.875
Talk to Jun Kyung and Jun Seo.

441
00:30:12.954 --> 00:30:15.267
Yes. I see.

442
00:30:16.888 --> 00:30:19.354
You must be tired of hearing all this.

443
00:30:23.132 --> 00:30:26.155
- Congratulations!
- You earned it.

444
00:30:27.485 --> 00:30:29.875
Do I deserve congratulations
to get a job at this age?

445
00:30:29.875 --> 00:30:31.635
Entering a public corporation is not easy.

446
00:30:31.635 --> 00:30:33.604
Win the real estate lottery
It's also difficult.

447
00:30:33.604 --> 00:30:36.310
I never thought I'd have a day like this.

448
00:30:36.909 --> 00:30:38.254
And you?

449
00:30:38.254 --> 00:30:40.178
What's so special about being an adjunct?

450
00:30:40.178 --> 00:30:42.660
It's keeping the students happy,
see the humor of the teachers.

451
00:30:42.660 --> 00:30:45.536
It sounds exhausting.
You are doing your PhD and teaching.

452
00:30:45.536 --> 00:30:48.710
Still, Professor Song takes care of you.

453
00:30:48.710 --> 00:30:50.790
I'm always the weird one.

454
00:30:55.657 --> 00:30:57.463
One second.

455
00:30:58.477 --> 00:31:00.050
Hello.

456
00:31:02.757 --> 00:31:04.489
True, it is today.

457
00:31:05.010 --> 00:31:06.947
Did you forget the anniversary of Mom's death?

458
00:31:06.947 --> 00:31:08.831
No, I didn't forget.

459
00:31:08.831 --> 00:31:11.331
I knew it, really.

460
00:31:11.331 --> 00:31:12.461
It just happened to me.

461
00:31:12.461 --> 00:31:14.087
You forgot.

462
00:31:14.700 --> 00:31:16.900
Anyway, come home at six.

463
00:31:17.371 --> 00:31:18.428
In fact,

464
00:31:18.428 --> 00:31:20.068
I'm with friends. It's been a long time.

465
00:31:20.068 --> 00:31:21.737
And?

466
00:31:21.737 --> 00:31:23.360
OK that's fine.

467
00:31:28.068 --> 00:31:29.409
I don't understand.

468
00:31:29.409 --> 00:31:31.389
- Hello, Jun Kyung.
- Hello.

469
00:31:33.776 --> 00:31:35.575
You look pretty today.

470
00:31:36.295 --> 00:31:38.569
The last time the expenditure was 50,000 won,

471
00:31:38.569 --> 00:31:41.279
and he only paid 30,000. I covered the rest.

472
00:31:41.279 --> 00:31:42.963
Hey, don't invite him next time.

473
00:31:42.963 --> 00:31:44.450
It's uncomfortable.

474
00:31:44.450 --> 00:31:46.055
Come on.

475
00:31:46.055 --> 00:31:48.633
People can be out of money sometimes.

476
00:31:48.633 --> 00:31:50.084
That's fine when you're at school.

477
00:31:50.084 --> 00:31:51.322
Seriously,

478
00:31:51.322 --> 00:31:53.086
Why are you a teaching assistant?

479
00:31:53.086 --> 00:31:55.290
Do you want to be adjunct or something?

480
00:31:55.290 --> 00:31:57.176
If you want to be a teacher,

481
00:31:57.176 --> 00:31:59.201
He should have taken care of his notes.

482
00:31:59.201 --> 00:32:02.166
He couldn't even graduate on time.

483
00:32:02.166 --> 00:32:05.779
He does it because he doesn't know how to do anything else.

484
00:32:05.779 --> 00:32:08.252
Have you ever tried to get a job?

485
00:32:08.252 --> 00:32:10.496
It doesn't even have a TOEIC score.

486
00:32:10.496 --> 00:32:12.673
Maybe he's just afraid.

487
00:32:12.673 --> 00:32:15.555
He knows well that he is nobody.

488
00:32:16.076 --> 00:32:18.560
I don't mind.

489
00:32:18.560 --> 00:32:21.656
Just tell him to pay his share.

490
00:32:24.248 --> 00:32:26.598
Don't talk like that behind his back,

491
00:32:26.598 --> 00:32:28.427
finish it.

492
00:32:30.497 --> 00:32:32.657
<i>Your transaction is being processed.</i>

493
00:32:37.566 --> 00:32:41.265
[Cash withdrawal: 70,000 won
Balance: 87,208 won]

494
00:32:45.175 --> 00:32:46.659
Hey, where did you go?

495
00:32:46.659 --> 00:32:48.859
The food is cold, eat.

496
00:32:51.466 --> 00:32:53.278
It's the 20,000 won I owed you last time.

497
00:32:53.278 --> 00:32:55.073
and 50,000 won today.

498
00:32:55.073 --> 00:32:56.273
Alright?

499
00:32:58.126 --> 00:32:59.326
That?

500
00:32:59.986 --> 00:33:01.686
I asked if it's okay.

501
00:33:03.293 --> 00:33:04.493
Yes.

502
00:33:07.713 --> 00:33:10.277
Hey, your bag...

503
00:33:10.277 --> 00:33:12.230
You forgot your bag.

504
00:33:21.530 --> 00:33:23.183
Yun Ju!

505
00:33:23.183 --> 00:33:24.596
Hello.

506
00:33:24.596 --> 00:33:27.590
So long!

507
00:33:27.590 --> 00:33:30.107
Look at this awkward hug.

508
00:33:30.107 --> 00:33:31.864
What do you have to worry about?

509
00:33:31.864 --> 00:33:33.690
A return recital after moving

510
00:33:33.690 --> 00:33:35.657
and everyone will fight to hire her
as a teacher.

511
00:33:35.657 --> 00:33:38.267
And if you get tired, you may simply not work.

512
00:33:38.267 --> 00:33:39.401
I know.

513
00:33:39.401 --> 00:33:42.457
Worry about her
It's the most useless thing in the world.

514
00:33:42.457 --> 00:33:43.911
You should have stayed in Germany.

515
00:33:43.911 --> 00:33:45.541
You're messing with the natural order here.

516
00:33:45.541 --> 00:33:47.854
- Don't exaggerate.
- Exaggerate?

517
00:33:47.854 --> 00:33:50.345
Our environment is brutal these days.
It's ruthless.

518
00:33:50.345 --> 00:33:51.405
Yes.

519
00:33:51.405 --> 00:33:53.662
Of all of us, Do Hyun is the popular one.

520
00:33:53.662 --> 00:33:56.369
In fact, I wrote to him today
to ask him if he would come.

521
00:33:56.369 --> 00:33:58.086
He said he couldn't, he's recording today.

522
00:33:58.086 --> 00:33:59.256
- Recording?
- Yes.

523
00:33:59.256 --> 00:34:00.489
- A weekend?
- Yes.

524
00:34:00.489 --> 00:34:01.653
Wow,

525
00:34:01.653 --> 00:34:03.866
must be in high demand.

526
00:34:06.182 --> 00:34:09.796
Hey, Do Hyun and I dated freshman year.

527
00:34:09.796 --> 00:34:13.168
It was a long time ago, they can talk about it.

528
00:34:14.342 --> 00:34:15.782
Is that okay with you?

529
00:34:16.722 --> 00:34:19.233
I saw him a few days ago,

530
00:34:19.233 --> 00:34:21.171
we are very well.

531
00:34:21.171 --> 00:34:23.031
What is that relaxed energy?

532
00:34:23.031 --> 00:34:25.587
Are we in Hollywood or something?

533
00:34:25.587 --> 00:34:28.054
Are you back to stay?

534
00:34:29.827 --> 00:34:32.773
I thought about it a lot before coming back.

535
00:34:34.207 --> 00:34:36.271
But yes, I decided to live here.

536
00:34:36.271 --> 00:34:37.907
Good for you.

537
00:34:38.794 --> 00:34:40.705
It's disappointing,

538
00:34:40.705 --> 00:34:42.734
but I understand.

539
00:34:42.734 --> 00:34:44.471
My patients' water breaks
from one moment to the next,

540
00:34:44.471 --> 00:34:46.294
Births are scheduled suddenly.

541
00:34:46.827 --> 00:34:50.547
I also missed plans with you many times.

542
00:34:51.027 --> 00:34:53.267
Thank you for understanding.

543
00:34:53.267 --> 00:34:54.574
Alright.

544
00:34:54.574 --> 00:34:56.387
Good luck with the recording.

545
00:34:56.974 --> 00:34:59.007
- Come on.
- Yes.

546
00:35:01.767 --> 00:35:03.540
He hadn't come for a long time.

547
00:35:07.040 --> 00:35:11.057
Sorry for leaving you with the kids.
All weekend, darling.

548
00:35:11.057 --> 00:35:14.397
You know what advertisers are like.
They change their minds all the time.

549
00:35:14.977 --> 00:35:16.317
Yes.

550
00:35:17.738 --> 00:35:19.568
It's okay, honey.

551
00:35:19.568 --> 00:35:21.816
I'll try to finish as quickly as I can.

552
00:35:21.816 --> 00:35:23.616
Okay, bye.

553
00:35:27.782 --> 00:35:29.082
Look at you.

554
00:35:29.862 --> 00:35:31.520
You were going to dress well

555
00:35:31.520 --> 00:35:34.969
and go to the wedding with your girlfriend,

556
00:35:34.969 --> 00:35:37.169
but the agenda exploded, right?

557
00:35:40.929 --> 00:35:42.222
Because?

558
00:35:46.076 --> 00:35:47.475
you and your wife

559
00:35:48.742 --> 00:35:50.482
they were so anxious

560
00:35:51.522 --> 00:35:53.922
like Jun Kyung and me.

561
00:35:54.716 --> 00:35:56.069
And how

562
00:35:56.802 --> 00:35:58.389
did they get married?

563
00:35:59.449 --> 00:36:01.606
Yes, we were afraid.

564
00:36:01.606 --> 00:36:03.989
There were many crises,

565
00:36:03.989 --> 00:36:05.369
but honestly,

566
00:36:06.049 --> 00:36:07.749
when I got married,

567
00:36:08.602 --> 00:36:11.561
All that anxiety disappeared.

568
00:36:14.416 --> 00:36:16.042
Sounds ridiculous, doesn't it?

569
00:36:20.836 --> 00:36:22.699
- Heavens.
- What nonsense.

570
00:36:22.699 --> 00:36:24.185
That hurts.

571
00:36:26.709 --> 00:36:28.354
If you remain considerate

572
00:36:28.354 --> 00:36:31.142
and worrying about the circumstances,
you will never get married.

573
00:36:31.142 --> 00:36:32.540
You need a little selfishness,

574
00:36:32.540 --> 00:36:34.597
put yourself first.

575
00:36:34.597 --> 00:36:36.669
That's the only way it works.

576
00:36:36.669 --> 00:36:39.382
How can I be selfish in my situation?

577
00:36:40.169 --> 00:36:41.353
Because?

578
00:36:41.353 --> 00:36:42.959
For Daniel?

579
00:36:42.959 --> 00:36:45.292
See? You can't anymore.

580
00:36:50.704 --> 00:36:53.258
I don't even know how she feels.

581
00:36:54.018 --> 00:36:55.413
Oh,

582
00:36:55.413 --> 00:36:57.438
you are very arrogant.

583
00:36:57.438 --> 00:37:00.515
How do you expect to know
What does someone feel without trying?

584
00:37:00.515 --> 00:37:04.355
If you want to know how it feels,
ask him the question.

585
00:37:04.355 --> 00:37:06.555
That way you will know for sure.

586
00:37:10.381 --> 00:37:11.939
That giraffe, Dr. Yeom,

587
00:37:11.939 --> 00:37:14.419
stretched out those long arms

588
00:37:14.419 --> 00:37:15.984
and lifted him up,

589
00:37:15.984 --> 00:37:19.252
and somehow it flew
and landed right in your arms.

590
00:37:19.252 --> 00:37:20.817
It's destiny.

591
00:37:23.645 --> 00:37:24.899
So,

592
00:37:24.899 --> 00:37:26.705
when will they do it?

593
00:37:27.446 --> 00:37:28.739
That?

594
00:37:28.739 --> 00:37:30.479
Get married?

595
00:37:30.479 --> 00:37:31.929
We haven't even talked about that.

596
00:37:31.929 --> 00:37:33.472
Come on.

597
00:37:33.472 --> 00:37:36.176
Blink once and you'll have 40.

598
00:37:36.176 --> 00:37:39.029
How come they have never talked about marriage?

599
00:37:39.729 --> 00:37:42.346
Why do we need something so expensive and formal

600
00:37:42.346 --> 00:37:44.716
that only causes problems for everyone?

601
00:37:44.716 --> 00:37:46.563
Do Hyun and I are fine like this.

602
00:37:46.563 --> 00:37:47.832
That's enough for us.

603
00:37:48.752 --> 00:37:52.752
But I don't think being well is enough.

604
00:37:55.567 --> 00:37:56.767
Oh.

605
00:37:57.680 --> 00:37:59.220
Jun Kyung?

606
00:38:01.807 --> 00:38:03.333
Hello.

607
00:38:04.273 --> 00:38:05.966
Oh.

608
00:38:05.966 --> 00:38:08.206
So, there was a recording.

609
00:38:10.320 --> 00:38:11.520
Sorry?

610
00:38:12.280 --> 00:38:14.666
I thought he lied about the recording

611
00:38:14.666 --> 00:38:17.126
just to go out with you.

612
00:38:21.223 --> 00:38:22.856
It's a joke.

613
00:38:28.111 --> 00:38:30.597
You look like you're coming from a wedding.

614
00:38:31.398 --> 00:38:34.437
They say that if you don't get married
six months after catching him,

615
00:38:34.437 --> 00:38:36.777
You can't for three years.

616
00:38:40.869 --> 00:38:42.795
That's a joke too.

617
00:38:46.697 --> 00:38:49.203
I guess we'll meet again, right?

618
00:38:59.964 --> 00:39:01.931
Oh.

619
00:39:01.931 --> 00:39:04.424
That really crosses the line.

620
00:39:05.124 --> 00:39:07.456
It doesn't filter anything,

621
00:39:07.456 --> 00:39:10.071
He just says what comes to mind.

622
00:39:10.071 --> 00:39:12.441
It wasn't my fault I got angry at that moment.

623
00:39:12.441 --> 00:39:14.114
It was hers.

624
00:39:14.811 --> 00:39:16.248
See?

625
00:39:16.248 --> 00:39:18.016
Still not thinking about getting married?

626
00:39:18.016 --> 00:39:20.762
A very strong rival has just appeared.

627
00:39:38.954 --> 00:39:41.074
Is that all you brought?

628
00:40:10.179 --> 00:40:11.666
Thanks to your mom,

629
00:40:12.486 --> 00:40:14.926
We are all together again.

630
00:40:16.320 --> 00:40:18.851
It was spring then,
but it was very cold.

631
00:40:18.851 --> 00:40:20.831
This year feels warmer, right?

632
00:40:20.831 --> 00:40:22.300
Yes.

633
00:40:22.300 --> 00:40:23.713
Yes.

634
00:40:27.134 --> 00:40:28.907
Did something happen?

635
00:40:33.767 --> 00:40:35.466
That? Nothing.

636
00:40:37.735 --> 00:40:39.868
Yes, nothing happened.

637
00:40:46.535 --> 00:40:48.382
Do you want us to have a drink together?

638
00:40:48.382 --> 00:40:49.728
We haven't done it in a while.

639
00:40:54.049 --> 00:40:55.354
Let's drink.

640
00:40:55.354 --> 00:40:56.709
Alright.

641
00:41:01.863 --> 00:41:03.108
You're not drinking, are you?

642
00:41:03.108 --> 00:41:05.261
- I'll just hold the glass.
- You came by car, right?

643
00:41:05.261 --> 00:41:06.392
- Yes.
- Okay.

644
00:41:06.392 --> 00:41:07.708
Take.

645
00:41:13.090 --> 00:41:15.290
Dad, is something wrong?

646
00:41:28.525 --> 00:41:31.844
I've been thinking

647
00:41:32.495 --> 00:41:35.186
If I should say this today,

648
00:41:35.186 --> 00:41:38.233
but both have been busy.

649
00:41:38.233 --> 00:41:40.572
And since we're all together now...

650
00:41:42.874 --> 00:41:44.667
I think it's time.

651
00:41:48.080 --> 00:41:49.587
Do you two

652
00:41:49.587 --> 00:41:52.140
will they get married?

653
00:41:53.860 --> 00:41:55.060
That?

654
00:41:56.946 --> 00:41:58.167
Come on.

655
00:42:02.998 --> 00:42:05.684
Will they really get married?

656
00:42:07.065 --> 00:42:09.931
No, I'm too old to get married.

657
00:42:13.045 --> 00:42:14.458
It's not that.

658
00:42:21.057 --> 00:42:22.430
I'm thinking

659
00:42:23.390 --> 00:42:25.203
to sell this house.

660
00:42:34.085 --> 00:42:35.663
Will you sell the house?

661
00:42:35.663 --> 00:42:37.256
Does that make sense?

662
00:42:37.745 --> 00:42:39.669
That's why dad wanted to talk about it.

663
00:42:39.669 --> 00:42:41.538
I object.

664
00:42:41.538 --> 00:42:42.882
And you?

665
00:42:48.722 --> 00:42:50.046
Dad wants to sell the house

666
00:42:50.046 --> 00:42:53.067
to set up camp with that woman.

667
00:42:53.067 --> 00:42:55.462
This is the house
where mom lived with all of us.

668
00:42:57.820 --> 00:42:59.426
Is that okay with you?

669
00:43:02.153 --> 00:43:03.486
Yeah?

670
00:43:07.966 --> 00:43:10.153
I asked you if that's okay with you.

671
00:43:10.153 --> 00:43:11.772
This is dad's house.

672
00:43:12.366 --> 00:43:14.552
You have the right to decide.

673
00:43:17.733 --> 00:43:19.140
but

674
00:43:19.140 --> 00:43:20.577
It seems sudden.

675
00:43:20.577 --> 00:43:23.503
How is this dad's house?
It's our house.

676
00:43:23.503 --> 00:43:24.564
No?

677
00:43:24.564 --> 00:43:27.055
So where will we go?

678
00:43:27.055 --> 00:43:30.745
Will we meet as a family
at barbecue places?

679
00:43:30.745 --> 00:43:32.075
Stop exaggerating

680
00:43:32.075 --> 00:43:34.049
He's just thinking about it.

681
00:43:34.049 --> 00:43:37.269
Just thinking about it is crazy!

682
00:43:38.489 --> 00:43:40.342
How could you, dad?

683
00:43:41.062 --> 00:43:43.739
This is the only home I have ever stayed in.

684
00:43:43.739 --> 00:43:46.939
I was born here, I've lived here my whole life.

685
00:43:46.939 --> 00:43:48.789
How can you do this to me?

686
00:43:48.789 --> 00:43:52.006
Obviously I'll get you a place to live.

687
00:43:52.006 --> 00:43:53.249
Clear.

688
00:43:55.211 --> 00:43:56.661
So I'm the problem.

689
00:43:56.661 --> 00:44:00.015
I'm the only one with no future or anywhere to go,

690
00:44:00.015 --> 00:44:01.671
so while I'm gone,
you can sell the house.

691
00:44:01.671 --> 00:44:02.696
It's not like that.

692
00:44:02.696 --> 00:44:04.126
Am I not family?

693
00:44:04.695 --> 00:44:07.128
- Am I just luggage?
- Hey.

694
00:44:15.336 --> 00:44:18.142
Today is the anniversary of Mom's death.

695
00:44:19.970 --> 00:44:21.569
How could you...?

696
00:44:27.757 --> 00:44:29.473
This wasn't even my room,

697
00:44:29.473 --> 00:44:31.108
It was dad's house, dad's room.

698
00:44:31.108 --> 00:44:35.948
Sorry, I've lived here for 29 years.

699
00:44:35.948 --> 00:44:37.861
Enough!

700
00:44:57.154 --> 00:44:58.585
I don't need a studio,

701
00:44:58.585 --> 00:45:00.851
I don't need your money.

702
00:45:00.851 --> 00:45:03.621
You and that woman will live happily ever after.

703
00:45:03.621 --> 00:45:05.294
A camp?

704
00:45:06.744 --> 00:45:08.895
It sounds fun.

705
00:45:08.895 --> 00:45:11.112
Yes, I will be happy with her,

706
00:45:11.112 --> 00:45:12.414
we will live well!

707
00:45:12.414 --> 00:45:14.240
Now go!

708
00:45:15.814 --> 00:45:17.764
How are you going to survive?

709
00:45:17.764 --> 00:45:20.616
You have no money or skills.

710
00:45:20.616 --> 00:45:21.680
Nothing!

711
00:45:21.680 --> 00:45:23.611
Will you live off your sister again?

712
00:45:23.611 --> 00:45:25.237
Is that the plan?

713
00:45:25.237 --> 00:45:26.630
Get out!

714
00:45:37.616 --> 00:45:39.630
Well, I mean...

715
00:45:39.630 --> 00:45:41.474
Jun Seo.

716
00:45:41.474 --> 00:45:43.083
Jun Seo!

717
00:46:14.841 --> 00:46:17.041
What did I do so wrong?

718
00:46:19.141 --> 00:46:20.864
I worked until I was tired,

719
00:46:20.864 --> 00:46:22.217
I bought this house,

720
00:46:22.217 --> 00:46:25.117
and now I want to sell it...

721
00:46:26.863 --> 00:46:29.063
and find my own happiness.

722
00:46:31.077 --> 00:46:33.277
Is that a crime?

723
00:46:46.729 --> 00:46:48.422
I don't know well.

724
00:46:53.357 --> 00:46:54.816
Leave.

725
00:47:16.046 --> 00:47:18.379
<i>There were four of us in that house.</i>

726
00:47:20.460 --> 00:47:23.533
<i>One day, suddenly we became three...</i>

727
00:47:26.574 --> 00:47:28.521
<i>then in two...</i>

728
00:47:34.137 --> 00:47:36.143
<i>and now, there was only one left.</i>

729
00:47:40.031 --> 00:47:41.964
<i>Can we still...</i>

730
00:47:44.811 --> 00:47:46.364
<i>call it family...</i>

731
00:47:49.571 --> 00:47:52.077
<i>even if there is only one left?</i>

732
00:47:54.908 --> 00:47:57.434
<i>The number you dialed is not available.</i>

733
00:48:01.776 --> 00:48:03.531
[Phone call]

734
00:48:04.950 --> 00:48:06.150
[My son]

735
00:48:10.451 --> 00:48:14.291
[My dad]

736
00:48:20.394 --> 00:48:22.594
Are you really not going to answer?

737
00:48:33.543 --> 00:48:35.643
What could I say?

738
00:48:37.990 --> 00:48:40.490
I didn't do anything wrong.

739
00:48:40.490 --> 00:48:42.690
I didn't say anything bad.

740
00:48:44.242 --> 00:48:46.675
Dad will say he's sorry again.

741
00:48:48.821 --> 00:48:51.467
And now I don't want to say I'm fine.

742
00:49:00.746 --> 00:49:03.119
Everyone supported me...

743
00:49:06.046 --> 00:49:08.886
even if it was a burden and a nuisance.

744
00:49:10.219 --> 00:49:12.285
Everyone knew it...

745
00:49:14.546 --> 00:49:16.959
and I was the only one who didn't know.

746
00:49:20.213 --> 00:49:21.939
Like an idiot...

747
00:49:24.679 --> 00:49:26.519
I'm the last one to notice.

748
00:49:31.675 --> 00:49:33.448
When I was little,

749
00:49:34.749 --> 00:49:37.982
people always called you
"Jun Kyung's mom."

750
00:49:40.869 --> 00:49:43.469
Why didn't they ever call you?
"Jun Seo's mom"?

751
00:49:44.369 --> 00:49:45.776
I thought

752
00:49:46.943 --> 00:49:49.729
which was because Jun Kyung had been born first.

753
00:49:51.308 --> 00:49:53.408
but everyone knew

754
00:49:54.962 --> 00:49:58.142
that he was smart and did well in school

755
00:49:58.142 --> 00:50:00.041
and that I was the stupid one.

756
00:50:01.022 --> 00:50:02.668
The useless one.

757
00:50:06.402 --> 00:50:09.115
Were you ashamed of me too, mom?

758
00:50:09.115 --> 00:50:10.755
Why would I do it?

759
00:50:11.602 --> 00:50:13.633
You are the most beautiful thing in the world

760
00:50:13.633 --> 00:50:15.869
for me.

761
00:50:16.895 --> 00:50:19.155
You are what makes me most proud.

762
00:50:21.688 --> 00:50:24.006
Don't say that.

763
00:50:24.006 --> 00:50:26.206
That's why I hate you more than anyone.

764
00:50:27.015 --> 00:50:28.580
You should have scolded me sometimes.

765
00:50:28.580 --> 00:50:31.828
You always said it was good,
and that's why I ended up like this.

766
00:50:36.164 --> 00:50:38.170
Do you know how I feel?

767
00:50:42.865 --> 00:50:44.811
How could I not know?

768
00:50:46.152 --> 00:50:48.011
You don't know how to hide

769
00:50:48.011 --> 00:50:49.998
your feelings.

770
00:51:02.370 --> 00:51:04.570
What are you doing here?

771
00:51:05.425 --> 00:51:08.557
The field has been closed for a long time.

772
00:51:08.557 --> 00:51:10.230
Go away.

773
00:51:12.211 --> 00:51:13.617
Lord...

774
00:51:17.337 --> 00:51:19.661
I have nowhere to go.

775
00:51:19.661 --> 00:51:21.114
That?

776
00:51:21.114 --> 00:51:22.667
Go away.

777
00:51:40.959 --> 00:51:42.516
Hello, Daniel.

778
00:51:42.516 --> 00:51:44.636
What's happening at this time?

779
00:51:45.692 --> 00:51:47.759
Wait a second.

780
00:51:50.552 --> 00:51:52.272
<i>It's me, Im Yun Ju.</i>

781
00:51:54.612 --> 00:51:57.698
<i>I've been thinking about what happened today.</i>

782
00:51:58.192 --> 00:52:02.025
<i>It seems that you misunderstood
a harmless joke.</i>

783
00:52:06.242 --> 00:52:08.692
Are we close enough to joke like that?

784
00:52:08.692 --> 00:52:11.725
That's why I called you, I wanted to apologize.

785
00:52:15.816 --> 00:52:19.016
Is this an apology I should accept?

786
00:52:19.016 --> 00:52:20.899
<i>If you do not accept it,</i>

787
00:52:20.899 --> 00:52:23.212
I can't do anything.

788
00:52:25.039 --> 00:52:27.799
<i>It looks like you're driving, I'm going to hang up.</i>

789
00:52:30.732 --> 00:52:32.865
What's wrong with him?

790
00:52:36.426 --> 00:52:37.842
Hey!

791
00:52:37.842 --> 00:52:39.460
Roll down the window!

792
00:52:39.460 --> 00:52:40.808
I said put it down!

793
00:52:41.338 --> 00:52:43.456
The traffic light changed centuries ago.
Why are you still standing?

794
00:52:43.456 --> 00:52:44.978
Crazy bitch.

795
00:52:44.978 --> 00:52:46.282
That?

796
00:52:46.282 --> 00:52:48.802
I'm sorry.

797
00:52:48.802 --> 00:52:50.548
Drive better next time.

798
00:53:02.698 --> 00:53:03.741
Hey.

799
00:53:03.741 --> 00:53:06.508
You call that an apology?

800
00:53:06.508 --> 00:53:09.198
Do you pretend to be nice

801
00:53:09.198 --> 00:53:11.165
just to feel better?

802
00:53:11.165 --> 00:53:14.262
If you're going to apologize, do it well.
If not, don't bother.

803
00:53:14.262 --> 00:53:17.081
And stop smiling, you only make it worse.

804
00:53:18.261 --> 00:53:19.799
What the hell...?

805
00:53:19.799 --> 00:53:21.395
Honey, come on.

806
00:53:21.395 --> 00:53:23.135
- Fast.
- OK.

807
00:53:50.165 --> 00:53:51.631
They are crazy.

808
00:54:20.575 --> 00:54:23.165
This woman bumped into us on purpose!

809
00:54:23.165 --> 00:54:25.306
Well, wait a moment.

810
00:54:25.306 --> 00:54:27.495
You keep saying "wait."

811
00:54:27.495 --> 00:54:29.463
It takes forever, damn.

812
00:54:29.463 --> 00:54:31.928
Sir, please stop cursing.

813
00:54:42.276 --> 00:54:44.729
This was not intentional.

814
00:54:48.114 --> 00:54:50.814
That? How was it not intentional?

815
00:54:51.324 --> 00:54:53.854
He blocked his lane on purpose.

816
00:54:53.854 --> 00:54:55.288
You can see it here.

817
00:54:55.288 --> 00:54:57.661
- How was I going to avoid that?
- No, she...

818
00:54:58.568 --> 00:55:01.828
He didn't move when the light changed.

819
00:55:01.828 --> 00:55:03.605
I was in a hurry.

820
00:55:03.605 --> 00:55:07.085
When in a hurry,
Does he insult and drive aggressively?

821
00:55:07.085 --> 00:55:09.162
No! This woman...

822
00:55:09.162 --> 00:55:10.992
Okay, let's stop.

823
00:55:10.992 --> 00:55:12.606
If you're going to fine us, do it quickly,

824
00:55:12.606 --> 00:55:14.019
Or let the insurance take care of it.

825
00:55:14.019 --> 00:55:15.972
Talking to her is useless.

826
00:55:16.759 --> 00:55:19.176
This can't be handled
with a fine or insurance.

827
00:55:19.176 --> 00:55:21.476
Threatening driving
It's not a traffic violation.

828
00:55:21.476 --> 00:55:24.322
It is criminal intimidation according to the Penal Code.

829
00:55:24.322 --> 00:55:25.522
Curse.

830
00:55:29.932 --> 00:55:32.778
After a hard day with only difficult people,

831
00:55:32.778 --> 00:55:35.331
you end up meeting someone
that gives you comfort.

832
00:55:36.945 --> 00:55:38.191
Sorry?

833
00:55:39.905 --> 00:55:42.018
I was just happy to see you.

834
00:55:42.965 --> 00:55:45.085
So you work around here.

835
00:55:46.292 --> 00:55:48.932
How strange to meet like this.

836
00:55:48.932 --> 00:55:52.038
My dad lives nearby, he was just passing by.

837
00:55:57.152 --> 00:55:59.259
So your name is Won Young.

838
00:56:02.239 --> 00:56:04.732
I knew the uniform looked good on you.

839
00:56:10.652 --> 00:56:12.179
How unexpected.

840
00:56:13.186 --> 00:56:15.263
I thought you were just a tough local

841
00:56:15.263 --> 00:56:17.529
who liked to drink alone,

842
00:56:18.185 --> 00:56:20.351
but you are an obstetrician and gynecologist.

843
00:56:21.246 --> 00:56:23.463
You have changed a lot,

844
00:56:23.463 --> 00:56:25.016
in a good way.

845
00:56:25.983 --> 00:56:28.746
You are the same.

846
00:56:28.746 --> 00:56:30.546
You are still bold and cool.

847
00:56:34.569 --> 00:56:35.869
Officer Oh.

848
00:56:38.436 --> 00:56:39.761
If the station contacts you,

849
00:56:39.761 --> 00:56:42.243
You will have to come to testify.

850
00:56:42.243 --> 00:56:43.509
OK.

851
00:56:44.743 --> 00:56:46.849
Do you mind if I contact you again?

852
00:56:48.609 --> 00:56:50.416
Of course not.

853
00:56:50.416 --> 00:56:52.480
I'll buy beer next time.

854
00:56:52.480 --> 00:56:53.882
Sounds good.

855
00:57:03.713 --> 00:57:05.913
Next time, I'll call you friend.

856
00:57:07.620 --> 00:57:08.933
OK.

857
00:57:18.258 --> 00:57:19.657
Who was it?

858
00:57:21.131 --> 00:57:22.871
A friend.

859
00:57:22.871 --> 00:57:24.161
A friend?

860
00:57:24.161 --> 00:57:26.110
He looked a little older than you.

861
00:57:26.718 --> 00:57:30.337
It's someone who accompanied me
when I was tired and alone.

862
00:57:30.337 --> 00:57:32.410
So yeah, she's a friend.
to which I am grateful.

863
00:57:39.874 --> 00:57:41.747
Great, thanks.

864
00:57:42.237 --> 00:57:44.138
- Good job!
- You did very well.

865
00:57:44.138 --> 00:57:45.659
- You too.
- Go home and rest.

866
00:57:45.659 --> 00:57:47.272
Thanks for your effort.

867
00:57:48.331 --> 00:57:49.774
Daniel.

868
00:57:49.774 --> 00:57:51.323
Sorry, I'm late.

869
00:57:51.323 --> 00:57:53.091
I brought your pizza...

870
00:57:53.091 --> 00:57:54.627
Good night, dad.

871
00:57:57.361 --> 00:57:58.654
Excellent.

872
00:58:06.929 --> 00:58:08.532
Hello.

873
00:58:08.532 --> 00:58:09.881
Hello.

874
00:58:11.002 --> 00:58:14.177
Why are you always surprised when you see me?

875
00:58:14.177 --> 00:58:16.157
Did I come to a place where I shouldn't?

876
00:58:17.070 --> 00:58:18.929
We already ate pizza,

877
00:58:18.929 --> 00:58:20.409
mom brought her.

878
00:58:28.085 --> 00:58:29.835
I won!

879
00:58:29.835 --> 00:58:32.482
I couldn't even eat well,

880
00:58:32.482 --> 00:58:34.815
but he still fed the fish.

881
00:58:36.755 --> 00:58:39.948
He must be very close friends with Jun Kyung,

882
00:58:40.709 --> 00:58:42.795
It makes me a little envious.

883
00:58:49.297 --> 00:58:50.771
Yun Ju.

884
00:58:50.771 --> 00:58:52.357
Yeah?

885
00:58:52.357 --> 00:58:54.901
That? Uncomfortable again?

886
00:58:54.901 --> 00:58:56.550
Do you feel uncomfortable?

887
00:59:00.129 --> 00:59:01.859
You're curious, right?

888
00:59:01.859 --> 00:59:04.122
You want to know why I came back to Korea.

889
00:59:07.163 --> 00:59:08.403
Yes.

890
00:59:09.215 --> 00:59:10.928
For Daniel, I suppose.

891
00:59:13.230 --> 00:59:14.496
Hey.

892
00:59:15.649 --> 00:59:18.415
Am I really that uncomfortable for you?

893
00:59:20.189 --> 00:59:22.501
Do you really think I spent my time in Germany

894
00:59:22.501 --> 00:59:24.593
just thinking about you

895
00:59:24.593 --> 00:59:26.599
and missing you?

896
00:59:30.337 --> 00:59:33.574
I dated people who liked me.

897
00:59:33.574 --> 00:59:35.820
The work was going well,

898
00:59:37.141 --> 00:59:38.738
and he was having a good time.

899
00:59:38.738 --> 00:59:40.000
Yes,

900
00:59:41.007 --> 00:59:42.654
I imagined it.

901
00:59:43.354 --> 00:59:44.927
But, Do Hyun...

902
00:59:47.260 --> 00:59:49.220
no matter how much I thought about it...

903
00:59:50.767 --> 00:59:52.760
I always came back to you.

904
00:59:57.521 --> 00:59:59.721
I came back for you.

905
01:00:02.983 --> 01:00:04.856
I want to try again with you.

906
01:00:52.263 --> 01:00:54.409
<i>This time I will manage alone.</i>

907
01:00:54.409 --> 01:00:55.450
<i>Why?</i>

908
01:00:55.450 --> 01:00:59.108
<i>To take revenge for the humiliation
from my dad and my sister.</i>

909
01:00:59.108 --> 01:01:01.928
<i>Don't tell my dad, please.</i>

910
01:01:01.928 --> 01:01:04.201
<i>Never tell him.</i>

911
01:01:05.188 --> 01:01:07.153
<i>Come here...</i>

912
01:01:07.153 --> 01:01:09.413
<i>Do you think we're rushing?</i>

913
01:01:09.962 --> 01:01:11.008
<i>Jin Ho.</i>

914
01:01:11.008 --> 01:01:12.681
<i>Are you still upset?</i>

915
01:01:12.681 --> 01:01:14.319
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

916
01:01:14.319 --> 01:01:16.852
<i>I think I was a little sensitive.</i>

917
01:01:16.852 --> 01:01:18.306
<i>Ha Yeong!</i>

918
01:01:18.306 --> 01:01:20.019
<i>Ha Yeong!</i>

919
01:01:20.019 --> 01:01:22.785
<i>When I was playing before,
It brought back old memories.</i>

920
01:01:22.785 --> 01:01:24.956
<i>Me too.</i>

921
01:01:25.565 --> 01:01:28.260
<i>Do Hyun is still Daniel's dad.</i>

922
01:01:28.260 --> 01:01:30.064
<i>Parents and children
They can't choose each other,</i>

923
01:01:30.064 --> 01:01:31.358
<i>and they can't be strangers either.</i>

924
01:01:31.358 --> 01:01:32.630
<i>What are you trying to say?</i>

925
01:01:32.630 --> 01:01:35.053
<i>If you were me, what would you do?</i>

926
01:01:35.053 --> 01:01:37.113
<i>Wouldn't you want to break it?</i>

